  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Operations Executive (Scheduling)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>The Smart Series vision is to create a better everyday life through the use of smart home devices. We do this by offering a wide range of smart home products and excellent customer service through all forms of sales channels. The Smart Series takes pride in empowering our staff to make decisions on behalf of the company and provide them with a high level of independence.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Manage installer schedules, routes, and logistics to support smooth installations and after-sales service for customers and resellers.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage daily installer schedules from Tuesday to Saturday to ensure timely installations</li><li>Optimize installer routes to reduce travel time and increase efficiency</li><li>Handle last-minute cancellations and rescheduling to maintain smooth operations</li><li>Collaborate with team to resolve urgent installation issues promptly</li><li>Provide backup support for after-hours emergency installation calls</li><li>Communicate installation estimated time of arrival (ETA) clearly to customers and resellers</li><li>Coordinate with team to prepare locks and spare parts for installations</li><li>Ensure installers have all necessary items before dispatch to job sites</li><li>Update appointment systems and installation logs accurately to maintain records</li><li>Track installer performance metrics and report any issues to management for resolution</li></ul><p><strong>Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Organize and manage schedules and logistics to support installation operations effectively</li><li>Communicate clearly and coordinate with internal teams and external customers to resolve issues</li><li>Apply problem-solving skills to handle last-minute changes and emergencies in installation plans</li><li>Use scheduling software with basic technical literacy to update and maintain appointment systems</li></ul><p>The role is scheduled during standard office hours, with Sundays and one weekday off.</p>",
